  "body": "I have a contract `contractA` which has the function `func1`. \r\n\r\n`func1` uses the library function `func2`.  \r\n\r\n`funct2` emits the event, called `EventExample`.\r\n\r\nIn my test, I have the following:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nawait expect(`contractA`.func1()).to.emit(`contractA`, 'EventExample')\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error says: \r\n\r\n> Expected event \"EventExample\" to be emitted, but it doesn't exist in the contract. Please make sure you've compiled its latest version before running the test.\r\n\r\nIt seems like the problem is because event gets thrown from library. How do I make this work ? I don't know the library address and will not know. \r\n",
